Program: Free Thinking
Title: Deserts
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b07j43n1
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 5 Jul 2016
As Georgia O'Keeffe images of New Mexico go on display at Tate Modern Matthew Sweet discusses deserts with the author of White Sands, Geoff Dyer , Tanya Barson, curator of the exhibition and writer Laurence Scott. Georgia O'Keeffe runs at Tate Modern from 6 July - 30 October 2016 Geoff Dyer is the author of White Sands: Experiences from the Outside World. It was read as Radio 4's Book of the Week last week which you can find on the Radio 4 website Laurence Scott is the author of The Four-Dimensional Human Producer: Jacqueline Smith. Show less